The paper presents a corpus for building cross-domain, general-purpose database querying dialogue systems, which involves natural language processing, database management, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.DB (Databases), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
